<!--
SPEAKER NOTES — Slide 4: AI Solved Execution

Here's the dirty secret that no one talks about in AI webinars.

GitHub Copilot is writing code. Azure DevOps pipelines are running. Infrastructure is being provisioned in minutes. The green column? Mostly solved. Not perfectly — but well enough.

The gold column is where your release train is stuck.

I was talking to a senior architect at a large private bank here in Mumbai. His team had GitHub Copilot. Great. They were generating code 40% faster. But they still couldn't ship faster because... the architecture review board met once a month. Once. A month.

You have a Ferrari engine and a traffic signal that only turns green on the 15th of every month. That's the real problem.

The gold column is not going away. You still *need* human judgment on direction and quality. But right now, those decisions are happening in meetings, in emails, in Slack threads — they're undocumented, unrepeatable, and every new engineer has to figure them out again from scratch.

AIDLC is about taking those decisions and encoding them. Write them down once, give them to an agent, and let the agent apply them at machine speed. The human becomes the validator, not the bottleneck.

That's the shift.
-->

