<!--
SPEAKER NOTES — Slide 7: Maturity Model

I want to be honest with you here. Most organisations in this room are at L1. Some are touching L2. Very few are at L3. And L4 is the research frontier.

And that's completely fine. The point is not to jump from L1 to L4 tomorrow. The point is to know where you are, and take the next step.

L1: You've enabled GitHub Copilot. Developers love it. They're writing code faster. You're measuring individual productivity. That's the starting point.

L2: Your team has started writing Copilot custom instructions — "always follow our REST API standards," "use our approved libraries." You're encoding decisions. You've moved from individual productivity to team leverage.

L3: Agents are doing whole workflows. A developer opens an issue, a Copilot agent generates a full PR with tests. The human reviews. If it's good, merge. This is where 4x velocity starts showing up in your DORA metrics.

L4: This is where agents are looking at how the process is running and suggesting improvements. "Hey, your test coverage drops every Friday afternoon — want me to add a gate?" This is 2026 territory.

Quick question for the room — how many of you have written any Copilot custom instructions for your team? 

[Pause for hands]

That's L2. You're already on the journey. What we're here to do is help you accelerate it.
