Step 4: I confirm in the PR. One comment: "Approved." That triggers the OIDC-authenticated deployment. No passwords. No service principal credentials in environment variables.

And post-deploy: git-ape validates. Endpoint reachable? Yes. HTTPS? Yes. App Insights? Connected. 

[After demo]: From prototype to production, in minutes, with a full compliance paper trail. That run is now saved in .azure/deployments/ — your next audit is going to be surprisingly easy.
