<!--
SPEAKER NOTES — Slide 15: Microsoft Stack

This is the full stack we're working with. Three layers.

Intent layer: This is where human decisions get expressed. Copilot Workspace lets you describe a feature in plain English and watch it decompose into specs. Azure AI Foundry lets you connect multiple AI models and evaluate which one is best for a given task. Copilot Spaces lets you curate the context — what documentation, what patterns, what constraints — that agents work from.

Execution layer: This is where the work happens. The Copilot Coding Agent runs autonomously — picks up issues, writes code, creates PRs. GitHub Actions provides the orchestration backbone. And git-ape is the deployment intelligence layer — it handles Azure deployments with all the security and compliance built in.

Governance layer: This is what makes enterprise adoption safe. Defender for DevOps integrates security scanning directly into your GitHub pipelines. Azure Policy acts as the final enforcement layer on the cloud side. GitHub Advanced Security catches vulnerabilities, exposed secrets, and dependency risks in the code itself.

Everything here is Microsoft and GitHub. If you're already paying for GitHub Enterprise or Microsoft 365 E5, much of this is already available to you. git-ape is open source — free to use, free to customise.

The question is not whether you have the tools. The question is whether you have the specs.
-->

