TAKEAWAYS
Remember these five things.
1
Execution is solved. Specification is your new competitive advantage.
2
AIDLC encodes human decisions into agent specs — stage by stage.
3
GitHub Copilot + AI Foundry: idea to prototype in minutes, not sprints.
4
git-ape: prototype to production with compliance built in.
5
Measure with DORA. What you don't measure, you can't mature.

<!--
SPEAKER NOTES — Slide 19: Takeaways

We're almost out of time. Let me give you five things to take home.

One: Execution is solved. Your developers are no longer the bottleneck. The bottleneck is decision-making — direction, standards, specs. If your engineering managers are still measured on how fast developers write code, change that metric now.

Two: AIDLC is not a tool you buy. It's a methodology you adopt. Start small. Pick one stage. Write down one decision. Give it to an agent. Measure the result. Repeat.

Three: The idea-to-prototype journey is already here. We showed it to you today. If your teams aren't using Copilot Workspace for feature development yet, that's two to three sprints of productivity you're leaving on the table every month.

Four: git-ape closes the prototype-to-production gap. The security and compliance that used to take weeks of review cycles is now built into the deployment pipeline itself. And it's open source — github.com/Azure/git-ape. Clone it tonight.

Five: If you're not measuring DORA metrics, you don't know if you're improving. Deployment frequency. Lead time. Change failure rate. MTTR. These four numbers will tell you everything about your engineering health. Start tracking them.

